"Makoto!? Why are you here? I thought you had to help out at
the dojo after school, right?"

"The dojo?... Ah, oh! So you knew about it too, Mamoru!
That's right. Actually, I've been helping out at a friend's
dojo lately."

"But suddenly the acting master fell ill, you see? So the
dojo help has been called off for the entire week!"

"I see, that's how it is. So, are you spending today playing
with your fans?"

"No, I haven't told the girls about the dojo being off. It's
just... I thought I'd like to spend the afternoon with you
for a change."

"What!? So you mean... you've been waiting here for me in
secret, without telling your fans?"

"Y-Yes... If it's okay with you, would you like to go to the
downtown area? Of course, if you have other plans, feel free
to turn me down..."

"None! No, no! I don't have any plans at all! In fact, I'm
free all week!"

"Really? That's great! Then let's go out and have fun right
away!"

I never dreamed that I'd get to spend the afternoon with
Makoto. We played so intently that before we knew it, it was
pitch dark outside.

It was truly a fun day. What a happy day it was. As we
walked side by side, Makoto invited me to play again
tomorrow.

I was so happy that I agreed immediately. And from then on,
until the dojo reopened, we spent every afternoon together.

Although I wanted to ask about Suzuki, seeing Makoto's happy
face made me lose the urge to bring it up. And so, our happy
time passed by, and before we knew it, a week had gone by.
